tafsir[3]{c,v,t}:
  17,87,"excepting by some mercy of thy Lord; surly His favour to thee is great."
  17,89,"We have indeed turned about for men in this Koran every manner of similitude; yet most men refuse all but unbelief."
  17,96,"Say: 'God suffices as a witness between me and you; surely He is aware of and sees His servants.'"